        <APP>\vb <LEM>kṣatriyāḥ</LEM> \mssALL\msCa\msCb\msNa\msNb\Ed; kṣatriyaḥ \msNc</APP>
        <TR>Truth is the pilgrimage place for Brahmins. A battle is a pilgrimage place for Kṣatriyas.</TR>

%index_grammar: kṣatriyāḥ thought of as a Newar genitive?
%index_grammar: stem form

<TEXT> āryā tīrthaṃ tu vaiśyānāṃ śūdratīrthaṃ ca vai dvijāḥ||</TEXT> 19:41
        <APP>\vc <LEM>vaiśyānāṃ</LEM> \mssALL\msCa\msCb\msNa\msNb\msNc; vaiśānāṃ \Ed</APP>
        <APP>\vd <LEM>śūdra°</LEM> \mssALL\msCa\msCb\msNa\msNb\Ed; śaudra° \msNc\oo
                 <LEM>ca</LEM> \mssALL\msCa\msCb\msNb\msNc; tu \msNa\Ed</APP>
        <NOTE>Emend to kārya?</NOTE>
        <TR>Āryā[varta?] is the pilgrimage place for Vaiśyas. The Brahmins are the pilgrimage place of Śūdras.</TR>

%index_grammar: nominatives for genitive

